  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Current state: zero tests.** No `tests/` directory, no pytest/pytest-asyncio/respx in `requirements.txt`, no CI test job (`.github/` only — not checked but worth confirming). `fetchers.py`'s own docstring says \"the HTTP client is injectable so the parsing logic is unit-testable against mocked transports\" — the code was written to be testable, it just never got tests. ~197K lines total across the repo, but the hand-written app logic is `agent.py`, `cli.py`, `fetchers.py`, `filters.py`, `models.py`, `notify.py`, `pipeline.py`, `store.py`.\n\nRecommended setup first:\n```\npip install pytest pytest-asyncio\n```\n(`respx` isn't needed — `httpx.MockTransport` is sufficient since `httpx` is already a dependency and every fetcher takes an injected `client`.)\n\n---\n\n### 1. `models.py` — highest priority, zero coverage, pure logic\n\n**Untested:** `parse_posted_at`, `Job.key`, `Job.posted_dt`, `Job.content_hash`, `Job.to_row`.\n\n**Gaps / edge cases:**\n- Epoch-seconds vs epoch-milliseconds boundary (`1_000_000_000_000` cutoff) — nothing tests values just above/below it, or negative epochs.\n- ISO-8601 with `Z` suffix, with explicit offset, and *naive* ISO (must default to UTC per `dt.replace(tzinfo=timezone.utc)`).\n- Garbage strings (`\"Posted 3 Days Ago\"` — explicitly called out in the docstring as a real Workday value) → must return `None`, not raise.\n- Empty string / `None` input.\n- `content_hash` stability — same title/location/url/department must hash identically; changing any one of the four must change the hash; `raw` and `posted_at` must NOT affect the hash (currently excluded — no test asserts this).\n- `Job.key` uniqueness/format across source+company+external_id, including when `external_id` contains a colon (would corrupt the composite key `source:company:external_id` — parsing key back apart isn't done anywhere, but worth asserting the format is stable).\n- `to_row()` must drop `raw` and inject `key`/`content_hash`.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_and_none_return_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n        assert parse_posted_at(None) is None\n\n    def test_epoch_milliseconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332430\")  # Lever-style ms epoch\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_epoch_seconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332\")\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_epoch_boundary_1e12(self):\n        # exactly 1e12 must be treated as milliseconds, not seconds\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1000000000000\")\n        assert dt.year < 2000  # would be ~33658 if misread as seconds... assert it's NOT that\n\n    def test_iso8601_with_z_suffix(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_iso8601_naive_defaults_to_utc(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_iso8601_with_explicit_offset_preserved(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00+05:00\")\n        assert dt.utcoffset().total_seconds() == 5 * 3600\n\n    def test_unparseable_prose_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    def test_negative_epoch(self):\n        # ensure lstrip(\"-\").isdigit() branch doesn't crash on pre-1970 dates\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"-100\")\n        assert dt is not None\n\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def _job(self, **kw):\n        base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                     title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n        base.update(kw)\n        return Job(**base)\n\n    def test_key_format(self):\n        assert self._job().key == \"greenhouse:acme:1\"\n\n    def test_content_hash_stable_for_identical_fields(self):\n        assert self._job().content_hash == self._job().content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_title(self):\n        assert self._job().content_hash != self._job(title=\"Sr Engineer\").content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_ignores_posted_at_and_raw(self):\n        a = self._job(posted_at=\"2024-01-01\", raw={\"a\": 1})\n        b = self._job(posted_at=\"2024-06-01\", raw={\"a\": 2})\n        assert a.content_hash == b.content_hash\n\n    def test_posted_dt_none_when_unparseable(self):\n        assert self._job(posted_at=\"garbage\").posted_dt is None\n\n    def test_to_row_excludes_raw_includes_key_and_hash(self):\n        row = self._job(raw={\"secret\": True}).to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert row[\"key\"] == \"greenhouse:acme:1\"\n        assert \"content_hash\" in row\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `filters.py` — pure logic, zero coverage\n\n**Gaps / edge cases:**\n- Word-boundary regex matching: `include=[\"go\"]` should NOT match \"Django\" or \"Chicago\" (this is the whole point of `\\b`) — no test verifies the boundary actually works vs. naive substring match.\n- `exclude` takes precedence over `include` when both match — untested ordering.\n- Empty `include`/`exclude`/`locations` lists vs `None` (falsy check `if exclude:` — an empty list `[]` and `None` behave identically, but that's never asserted).\n- Case-insensitivity for keywords and locations.\n- `cutoff` behavior: job with **unparseable** `posted_at` must be **kept** even under a cutoff (explicit design choice per the comment) — this is the single most important behavior in the file and has no test.\n- `max_age_days` as a float string (`\"1.5\"`) — `float(max_age)` cast.\n- `max_age_days` of `0` (falsy — `if max_age:` means `0` disables the cutoff entirely, likely a real bug/surprise) — worth a test that documents current behavior either way.\n- Location substring matching (`\"San Francisco\"` matches `locations=[\"francisco\"]`) vs no match at all.\n- Special regex characters in include/exclude keywords (e.g. `\"C++\"`) — `re.escape` should protect this; add a regression test.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\ndef make_job(**kw):\n    base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                title=\"Software Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\",\n                location=\"San Francisco, CA\", department=\"Engineering\")\n    base.update(kw)\n    return Job(**base)\n\nclass TestMatch:\n    def test_include_word_boundary_excludes_substring_match(self):\n        # \"go\" must not match \"Django\"\n        j = make_job(title=\"Django Developer\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"go\"]) is False\n\n    def test_include_matches_whole_word(self):\n        j = make_job(title=\"Go Developer\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"go\"]) is True\n\n    def test_exclude_wins_over_include(self):\n        j = make_job(title=\"Senior Intern Engineer\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"engineer\"], exclude=[\"intern\"]) is False\n\n    def test_case_insensitive(self):\n        j = make_job(title=\"ENGINEER\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"engineer\"]) is True\n\n    def test_locations_substring_case_insensitive(self):\n        j = make_job(location=\"San Francisco, CA\")\n        assert match(j, locations=[\"francisco\"]) is True\n        assert match(j, locations=[\"seattle\"]) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_drops_old_dated_job(self):\n        old = make_job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30))\n                        .isoformat(timespec=\"seconds\"))\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n        assert match(old, cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_undated_job(self):\n        # design decision: unparseable posted_at must survive the cutoff\n        undated = make_job(posted_at=\"\")\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n        assert match(undated, cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_recent_job(self):\n        recent = make_job(posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n                           .isoformat(timespec=\"seconds\"))\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n        assert match(recent, cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n    def test_special_regex_chars_in_keyword_are_escaped(self):\n        j = make_job(title=\"C++ Engineer\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"C++\"]) is True\n\n\nclass TestFilterJobs:\n    def test_empty_rules_keeps_everything(self):\n        jobs = [make_job(), make_job(external_id=\"2\")]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n\n    def test_max_age_days_as_float_string(self):\n        old = make_job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=5))\n                        .isoformat(timespec=\"seconds\"))\n        assert filter_jobs([old], {\"max_age_days\": \"1.5\"}) == []\n\n    def test_max_age_days_zero_disables_cutoff(self):\n        # documents current behavior: `if max_age:` treats 0 as falsy\n        old = make_job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=999))\n                        .isoformat(timespec=\"seconds\"))\n        assert filter_jobs([old], {\"max_age_days\": 0}) == [old]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `store.py` — SQLite dedup, zero coverage, integration-shaped\n\nEasy to test in-memory (`Store(\":memory:\")` — note `sqlite3.connect(str(path))` handles that fine).\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `diff()`: new job → inserted + returned in `new`; unchanged job (same `content_hash`) on second run → not in either list, but `last_seen` bumped; changed job (different hash, same key) → returned in `changed`, row updated.\n- Migration path: opening a DB file that predates the `salary_range` column (`_migrate`) — untested; a regression here silently breaks upgrades for existing users.\n- `next_seq`: sequential