        "content": "\nEasy to test in-memory (`Store(\":memory:\")` — note `sqlite3.connect(str(path))` handles that fine).\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `diff()`: new job → inserted + returned in `new`; unchanged job (same `content_hash`) on second run → not in either list, but `last_seen` bumped; changed job (different hash, same key) → returned in `changed`, row updated.\n- Migration path: opening a DB file that predates the `salary_range` column (`_migrate`) — untested; a regression here silently breaks upgrades for existing users.\n- `next_seq`: sequential calls increment; first call on fresh meta table returns `1`; concurrent-safe behavior can at least be smoke-tested with threads even without full concurrency proof.\n- `added_since`: boundary is *strictly* greater than `ts` (off-by-one risk); ordering (`first_seen, company, title`).\n- `get_meta`/`set_meta`: missing key returns `None`; upsert overwrites existing value (`ON CONFLICT`).\n- `count()` on empty DB.\n- Context manager (`__enter__`/`__exit__`) actually closes the connection.\n\n```python\n",
